itle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/10/03 7:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1001.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Letters for a Zippus Maximor...</span><hr size=1> Greetings my dear friend and collegue of the Eldrich Collective.<br>
<br>
As you have already ventured from Ak'Anon and across the Ocean of Tears, I presume that you also know that you have been assigned a &quot;guardian&quot; of sorts.<br>
Being as inquisitive as always, I have managed to round up these two letters from drawers of our honourable King, concerning this Stoppelton that you are supposed to meet in Freeport. <br>
Do not worry, these are ofcourse not the original ones, but only a copy of them, so on one will know that I have sent you these letters.<br>
<br>
As you can read in the two letters, I am not sure which is more dangerous, your guardian or the dangers you will face on the journey. But I shall pray for your wellbeing in our Church, and encourage you to take caution, and not rely on anyone but yourself for protection. <br>
You have already learned much in the ways of Magic, and I hope that they will be enough to complete your mission and bring you back safely to our home.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
May Solusek Ro grant you the power to complete your mission.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Maric Gandehahl of the Eldrich Collective.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<br>
--------<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>A small square piece of paper written with hastily penned letters...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Salutations honourable King Ak'Anon!<br>
<br>
It is with a certain joy that I can inform you, that our &quot;thirsty&quot; and &quot;slightly enthusiastic&quot; friend of the Deep Muses, has been sent off to Halas.<br>
As you agreed, I had him understand that he is now the General of the 1st Clockwork Expeditionary Force, and that he would serve Ak'Anon in an honourable and meaningful way. So that clears the problem we had discussed earlier.<br>
Having him stationed in far, far away Halas should keep him occupied, which will leave us free to restore the pride and reputation, that the Paladins have lost due to this person, over the last year or so.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That letter was signed by the guildmaster of the Church of Deep Muses.<br>
<br>
--------<br>
<br>
This next one was written in human, but I have taken the liberty of translating it to Gnomish for you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>All hail in the name of the Tribunal!<br>
<br>
I shall be blunt and forward with you, King Ak'Anon. <br>
You have obviously &quot;assigned&quot; this drunkard Starkweather to assist us in our efforts to rid ourselves of the Ice goblin tribes. An honourable deed, I am sure, if it were not for the fact that this drunkard is causing us more trouble than the goblins.<br>
<br>
At first he has been trying to exercise his &quot;authority&quot; as a formal envoy of Ak'Anon...And I assure you, that any Gnome from the Steamfront Mountains, holds no authority in these lands.<br>
In addition to that, he has been rambling around Halas, completely drunk and causing more destruction, than a stampede of wild Mammoths could. Not to mention that he bores us all, with his obviously fictional war stories.<br>
 <br>
Thus I call upon you to withdraw him to your own lands of the Steamfront Mountains, or we shall exercise our swift justice upon him, and be sure to &quot;repay&quot; your favour.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
This was signed by a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Ilgor McAngus - Judge of the Tribunal</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Again, I wish a safe and pleasant journey, my friend. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maricgandehahl@firionavie>Maric Gandehahl</A> at: 6/10/03 7:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=generalstarkweather>General Starkweather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/11/03 3:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1001.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letters for a Zippus Maximor...</span><hr size=1> Greetings Zippus Maximor!<br>
<br>
It is with great pride that I can inform you, that the King himself have assigned me to assist and protect you in this mission you have undertaken to visit the Erudites of Odus, or whatever it is you librarians of the Eldrich Collective are up to. <br>
Being the General of the 1st Clockwork Expeditionary Force, I can assure you that I am quite capable of protecting you from whatever dangers we might find on our way. Except, maybe, from the hordes of young maidens that always follow in my wake.<br>
<br>
I have somewhat recently been assigned to assist the Barbarians of Halas, in their endeavour to rid the lands of the Ice goblin clans. They have been most pleased with my service, so pleased in fact that they have reached their goal within a matter of weeks after I arrived. <br>
So it seems that our King, have seen fit to assign me to this new mission.<br>
<br>
I look forward to assisting a member of the Eldrich Collective, and I am certain that you will be pleased with my swordsmanship, in addition to my many stories and anecdotes, which are most interesting and entertaining. In fact, I am sure that by now, the League of Antonican Bards, sing and tell tales of my bravery, valour and achievements. But then, I presume you have heard the legends already.<br>
<br>
At the docks of Freeport, I will await you, so we can start our trek across the Antonican continent and we should reach Odus within a week. Don't forget to bring your walking stick!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
At ease, Soldier!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>General of the 1st Clockwork Expeditionary Force<br>
Clockwork Crusader - Stoppelton Starkweather.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=littanydthule>LittanyDThule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/11/03 12:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1001.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letters for a Zippus Maximor...</span><hr size=1> Dear General Starkweather,<br>
