<br>
**********<br>
The Clockwork Army<br>
<br>
From out the gates of  Ak’Anon,  a clamour, shrill and loud,<br>
The Clockwork army marches, a daft unruly crowd,<br>
From Odus to the snows of Halas, where ever they will roam,<br>
From Calabis to Luclin, hear the cry of “Go Home Gnome!”<br>
<br>
With a drunkard for a general, they march in quest of wars,<br>
But some how their success rate is far more in finding bars,<br>
A raggle tag , a motley crew, a joke in poorest taste,<br>
Please shout a zone wide warning, they are in the Eastern Waste.<br>
<br>
In Halas, hailed as heros, if you listen to their tale,<br>
In fact the General did impress them with his endless thirst for ale,<br>
And as the MacQuaids bounced him, they wrote on his small and shiny dome<br>
In bright blue woad and ashes, just one plea, to “Go Home Gnome”.<br>
<br>
The Clockwork Army marches, quick! Put the clerics on alert!<br>
The clanking legend once more rides, someone will sure be hurt,<br>
Their eyes are red and fired up, is it the elven wine, or zeal?<br>
My sides may split from laughing, please throw me one more heal!<br>
<br>
So I’ll sing a song of valour, and I’ll sing a song of cheer,<br>
And if you need a merry giggle, I’ll sing for you to hear,<br>
Of the Clockwork Expedition, in truth a very funny poem,<br>
And please join me in the chorus as we all chant “Go Home Gnome!”<br>
<br>
Meledi Weaver<br>
