<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Dear Master Starpyre,<br>
<br>
I have completed my tasks in the Erudin Library, though I must say not without incident.  It seems my 'bodyguard' made quite a ruckus while we were in there, and some High Man named Sergian came in, quite irate with us.  I didn't think we were as loud, nor the dilemma as bad as he insists, but it seems he has deemed it necessary for us to redeem ourselves (I doubt this possible in his eyes).  I am afraid he is taking us off somewhere now with him, but where I am not sure.  I have only what little time before we set off to write this letter and one to the King regarding Stoppelton's activities here.<br>
<br>
Your Student,<br>
<br>
Zippus Maximor</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Frowning, Tobon Starpyre pens his reply and whistles for the bard, who takes it without word and nods before setting off.<br>
<br>
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
King Ak'anon, in his throne room, reads the letter from Zippus Maximor:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>To my Great King,<br>
<br>
M'lord, I apologize, but I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>must</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> inquire what I have done to earn your ire?!  Stoppelton is going to drive me mad if I continue in his company!  His overprotectiveness is mind numbing!  I cannot set foot outside my room without him in front of me with a sword explaining that assassins are likely on the nearby rooftops!<br>
<br>
I am begging you, please request him back, or at least that he give me some breathing space!<br>
<br>
Pleadingly yours,<br>
<br>
Zippus Maximor</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The King lets out a chuckle, and hands the letter to his aid to pen a reply. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zippusmaximor>Zippus Maximor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/15/03 1:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1001.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letters for a Zippus Maximor...</span><hr size=1> Another letter arrives at Ak'anon, addressed to Tobon Starpyre.  It is obviously written in haste:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Dear Master Starpyre,<br>
<br>
I have traveled to our first destination with this fool Sergian, and now my suspicions of his lunacy are confirmed.  We traveled to the lands of Velious, told that we were going to 'meet someone'.  Sergian apparently ditched Stoppelton in one of the bars of 'Thurgadin' and took me alone off.  I'm not complaining in that regard.  However, the company we sook was far from what I expected! <br>
<br>
At the entrance to Thurgadin, we were greeted by none other than an Erudite Heretic and two Tier'dal!  The horror!  Picking up quickly on Sergian's alias and simply not acknowledging my connections to the collective, I traveled to a set of caverns with them, nervous all the way.  <br>
<br>
It became clear after some time in the caverns that 'Littany', the Heretic, did not believe for a minute Sergian's alias was who he was, though Sergian seemed in denial that she could flush out his real identity.<br>
<br>
I'm writing this letter to you from Froststone, a lost Coldain city in the bottom of the caverns.  I shall keep you updated as long as I can, or until I'm killed because of an Erudite's mistake.<br>
<br>
Til next update,<br>
<br>
Zippus Maximor</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=generalstarkweather>General Starkweather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/16/03 9:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1001.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letters for a Zippus Maximor...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>At a table in the local tavern in Thurgadin, sits a Gnome clad in intricate clockwork armour. The table is almost full of empty glasses of ale, except for a little space infront of him, where he sits trying to write a letter...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Greetings master Reldnok!<br>
<br>
I have been following my mission to the very brink of perfection, and even though this dusty librarian of the Eldrich Collective, seems to be hell-bend on running head first into mortal danger, I have been more than successful in keeping him alive and well.<br>
I have still not grasped exactly what his mission is, but it seems to involve alot of travelling, and listening to the inane ramblings of two airheaded Erudites.<br>
<br>
